 development of a mass rank-and-file movement in the coalfield based around demands for a miners' minimum wage and, when this principle was won in March 1912, for an improved minimum wage. This book is of interest to academics, advanced students and lay people interested in political, social and economic history, political thought, economics, and industrial relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCoal minersxLabor unionsxHistoryxEnglandxDurham (County). 0aCoal minersxLabor unionszEnglandzDurham (County)xHistory. 0aIndustrial relationsxGovernment policyxHistoryxGreat Britain. 0aIndustrial relationsxGovernment policyzGreat BritainxHistory. 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh  aAgency.  aDurham Miner’s Association.  aIndependent Labour Party.  aLiberalism.  aStructure.  aminimum wage.  arank-and-file movement.  asocialism.  asyndicalism.1 aMates, Lewis H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499759540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997595423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997595/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles